.TH SOURCE2NATIVE 1 "@PROJECT_YEAR@" "source2native @PROJECT_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
source2native \- convert Debian packages to native source format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B source2native
[\fIOPTION\fR]... \fIpackage-root\fR...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B source2native
ensures that one or more Debian source trees use the
.BR "3.0 (native)"
source format instead of
.BR "3.0 (quilt)".
.PP
For each \fIpackage-root\fR (a directory containing
.BR debian/ ),
the tool:
.IP \(bu 2
writes
.B debian/source/format
as
.BR "3.0 (native)"
.IP \(bu 2
rewrites every
.B debian/changelog
header to drop the Debian revision suffix (for example
.BR "1.2.3-1"
becomes
.BR "1.2.3" )
.IP \(bu 2
optionally removes quilt-only files or upstream
.BR ".orig.tar.*"
archives
.IP \(bu 2
creates a git commit with message
.B "Changed source format to native."
when changes were made
.PP
Unless
.B \-\-no\-commit
is given and the tree is a git repository, the tool first runs
.BR "git stash"
to save local modifications, performs the conversion and commit on a clean
worktree, then runs
.BR "git stash pop"
to restore your previous changes. If
.B stash pop
fails because of merge conflicts, the autostash entry is dropped; resolve
conflicts in the worktree manually.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Show planned changes without modifying files, stashing, committing, or popping.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-commit
Apply file changes but do not create a git commit. The stash workflow is skipped.
.TP
.B \-\-drop\-quilt
Remove quilt-only paths:
.BR debian/patches ,
.BR debian/source/local-options ,
.BR debian/README.source ,
and
.BR debian/watch .
Without this option, remaining quilt artifacts are reported on stderr.
.TP
.B \-\-drop\-orig
Remove sibling
.BR "*.orig.tar.*"
files for the package. Without this option, found tarballs are reported on
stderr.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a short usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Print program version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Preview conversion of a package:
.PP
.nf
source2native -n ~/src/my-package
.fi
.PP
Convert and commit, also removing quilt metadata:
.PP
.nf
source2native --drop-quilt ~/src/my-package
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success, or no changes were required.
.TP
.B 1
A path was missing, git
.B stash pop
failed, or another subprocess error occurred.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dpkg-source (1),
.BR git-stash (1)
